<div class='post-outer'>
<div class='post hentry uncustomized-post-template' itemprop='blogPost' itemscope='itemscope' itemtype='http://schema.org/BlogPosting'>
<meta content='14902380' itemprop='blogId'/>
<meta content='2118533698084945092' itemprop='postId'/>
<a name='2118533698084945092'></a>
<h3 class='post-title entry-title' itemprop='name'>
<a href='http://soldier-ethicist.blogspot.com/2017/07/correcting-unethical-conduct-by.html'>Correcting Unethical Conduct by Superiors is Especially Challenging</a>
</h3>
<div class='post-header'>
<div class='post-header-line-1'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-body entry-content' id='post-body-2118533698084945092' itemprop='articleBody'>
<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on">
<span style="font-family: arial;"><span face=", &quot;arial&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , sans-serif" style="background-color: white; color: #333333; font-size: 16px;">The most troubling and challenging ethical situations I have faced in the Army involved misconduct by leaders who were senior to me.&nbsp;</span><span face=", &quot;arial&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , sans-serif" style="background-color: white; color: #333333; font-size: 16px;">The Army&#8217;s culture would improve if there were a shared understanding about all soldiers&#8217; duty to hold their leaders accountable to the Army&#8217;s ethical standards.</span><br />
<span face=", &quot;arial&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , sans-serif" style="background-color: white; color: #333333; font-size: 16px;"><br /></span>
<span face=", &quot;arial&quot; , &quot;helvetica&quot; , sans-serif" style="background-color: white; color: #333333; font-size: 16px;">See my June column in ARMY here: <a href="https://www.ausa.org/articles/when-%E2%80%98moral-compasses%E2%80%99-need-calibration" target="_blank">When "Moral Compasses" Need Calibration</a></span></span></div>
<div style='clear: both;'></div>
</div>
<div class='post-footer'>
<div class='post-footer-line post-footer-line-1'>
<span class='post-author vcard'>
</span>
<span class='post-timestamp'>
at
