<h2>About Me</h2>
<div class='widget-content'>
<a href='https://draft.blogger.com/profile/16027642894453539902'><img alt='My photo' class='profile-img' height='80' src='//3.bp.blogspot.com/-ERiprD5VCJs/WcxRIVkLCiI/AAAAAAAAJL4/FbF6TY4wS9MOqq2HIaGr_XCx1mUGIxZRgCK4BGAYYCw/s80/tri-photo%2B%25282%2529.jpg' width='80'/></a>
<dl class='profile-datablock'>
<dt class='profile-data'>
<a class='profile-name-link g-profile' href='https://draft.blogger.com/profile/16027642894453539902' rel='author' style='background-image: url(//draft.blogger.com/img/logo-16.png);'>
Pete Kilner
</a>
</dt>
<dd class='profile-data'>Highland Falls, New York, United States</dd>
<dd class='profile-textblock'>Retired Army officer; five short research deployments to Iraq (03, 07) and Afghanistan (09, 10, 11); Ph.D in Instructional Systems (Penn State); M.A. in Philosophy (Virginia Tech); B.S. in Political Science (West Point); founder of Core Ethics, LLC; married, father of four sons, two of whom have chosen to become Army officers.</dd>
</dl>
